Module org.example.my_project
Package org.example.my_project.BL

Class ModelExplorer

java.lang.Object
org.example.my_project.BL.ModelExplorer
public class ModelExplorer extends Object
ModelExplorer class is responsible for managing and updating the visual representation of the UML model in a TreeView. It allows adding, removing, and updating shapes and their connections in the model explorer.

    • modelUpdateOnLoad

      public void modelUpdateOnLoad(List<Shape> shapes)
      Updates the model explorer when the shapes are loaded from the diagram. This method organizes shapes into a tree structure based on their type.
      Parameters:
      shapes - The list of shapes to load into the model explorer.

    • addConnectionToModelExplorer

      Adds a connection between two shapes in the model explorer.
      Parameters:

      connectionName - The name of the connection.

      public javafx.scene.control.TreeItem<String> getModelExplorerItemAt(double x, double y)

      y - The y-coordinate of the shape.
      Returns:

    • printAllTreeItems

      public void printAllTreeItems()
      Prints all the tree items in the model explorer starting from the root. This method provides a hierarchical view of the items in the TreeView.
